        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>What’s going on inside a speaker?</strong></p><p>For anything that produces sound, there has to be a force that is applied to the sound source to deform or bend it to get it to vibrate. We identified what that force was for many instruments, but we never identified what the force was in the speaker to make it vibrate.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "B91CCeE36rshIzf2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Turn and talk</strong></p><ol><li>How could we investigate what is causing the speaker to vibrate? Once you&#x27;ve thought about this,</li><li>Watch this video of <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6MMwKN9TaVU\">a teacher dissecting a speaker</a>. </li><li>Make a Notice and Wonder chart in a new page in your notebook, like the example below.</li></ol>"
          ]
        }
      },
